`crates/ctx-brief/tests/` is the integration-test boundary for
`ctx_brief::runner::run` ā€” it validates the gatherā†’plan pipeline
end-to-end against fakes, giving downstream readers confidence that the
runner's public behavior (headless/interactive modes, error handling,
request-resolution fallback) is pinned by executable examples rather than
just documented.

`brief.rs` is the only test file; `common/` supplies the fake world it
runs against (`FakeFs`, `FakeClaude`, `seeded`, `cfg`). The coupling that
matters here: `brief.rs`'s call-count assumptions (how many `print` calls
per mode) must match what `common`'s `FakeClaude` was seeded to expect,
and both must track the real `runner::Config` shape and prompt paths ā€”
none of this is enforced by the compiler, only by these tests staying in
sync with `ctx_brief::runner`. The asserted output path
`.context/.reports/briefs/item.md` is a literal string shared across
test cases; a runner path-logic change breaks all of them at once.

No `intent.md` exists for this directory, so no divergence can be
assessed.